Nigerian-American controversial actress, Judith Opara Mazagwu, popularly known as Afrocandy, will join her siblings in her country home to pay her late mum, Mama Agatha Opara, last respect as well as give her a befitting burial. Afrocandy, who is also a citizen of America, will visit Nigeria next week for the burial arrangement billed to hold in Ugiri-Ike Ikeduru Local Government Area in Imo State, on April 30. According to the actress-cum-singer, the burial arrangement will commence with a lying-in-state at her maiden home, Mr Dialaekwe’s compound by 8:30 am. Afrocandy lost her mother on February 21 and broke the news on her social media handle about the development. Her fans and colleagues in the industry have since sympathised with her and also extended their condolences. The movie producer, who visited Nigeria last in 2014, hopes to return home for her mum’s burial, noting that she would also visit orphanage homes to give back to the underprivileged on behalf of her mother. She also hinted R that she would also engage in a media tour and shoot some new projects after her main mission to Nigeria.